\pard\f0\fs28    A distinctive variant occurs in Denmark (Jylland) with ascending branches 50-60 cm, and sericeous, 1-foliolate leaves on young twigs. It remains constant in cultivation and may deserve recognition as a further subspecies. Intermediates between it and subsp.{\i  scoparius} occur in Jylland due to hybridization following the introduction of the latter subspecies.
